definition.text: Use this command to add a new page to the Docs.

paragraphs.text: Syntax
Option 1:
docs.add Node to Project: Docs Page Name
Example:
docs.add Node to Superalgos: Binance API
Option 2:
docs.add Concept to Project: Docs Page Name
Example:
docs.add Concept to Superalgos: Two-way Reference
Option 3:
docs.add Topic to Project: Docs Topic Name->Docs Page Name->Docs Page Number
Example:
docs.add Topic to Superalgos: Docs Styles->Docs Text Style->1
Option 4:
docs.add Topic to Project: Docs Tutorial Name->Docs Page Name->Docs Page Number
Example:
docs.add Tutorial to Superalgos: How to Build Indicators->Intro->1
Option 5:
docs.add Review to Project: Docs Review Name->Docs Page Name
Example:
docs.add Review to Project: Superalgos Project Review->Superalgos Review - Great Project!
Parameters
Project: It's the project where the Node, Concept, Topic or Review is defined.
Docs Page Category: Node, Concept, Topic, Tutorial, or Review.
Docs Topic / Tutorial / Review Name: The name of the topic /tutorial /review to which the new page will belong.
Docs Page Name: For Nodes it is the type of node; for Concepts, the concept name; for Topics, the topic's page name, for Tutorials, the tutorial step name; for Reviews, the review page name.

Docs Page Numer: Optional. A page number to be assigned to the new page. The number affects the position in the corresponding table of contents only. If a Docs Page Number is not provided, the systems assign one.
